## Hard Rules

### Note-management — unified surfacing rules
Single source of truth: the `note-management` skill (`skills/note-management/SKILL.md`) owns `state/directives.json`.
- **Before surfacing anything** (task, email, Slack message, alert): `python3 skills/note-management/scripts/directives.py check "<text>" --scope <skill>`. If `surface: false`, drop.
- **When {{USER_PREFERRED_NAME}} says "done" / "snooze" / "always archive X" / "stop flagging X"**: add a directive immediately via `directives.py add` — same turn.
- **When {{USER_PREFERRED_NAME}} gives a forward note ("for tomorrow", "don't forget")**: `directives.py add --action remind --until <date> --match "<note>" --scope morning-brief`.
- Actions: `suppress` (never surface), `snooze --until DATE`, `archive` (auto-archive), `remind --until DATE` (surface once on date).
- Never hand-edit `state/directives.json`. Always use the CLI.

